# This file holds "examples" only. Safe to commit to Git. Do NOT put real keys here.
#
# Usage:
#   cp .env.example .env
#   then open .env and put your real key after OPENAI_API_KEY=
#
# The only file actually loaded is:  .env  (dot-env)

OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your_key_here
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000

# --- PDF = Docker TeX Live full only (no host latexmk/pdflatex/TinyTeX) ---
#
# Quick check (3 steps):
#   1) Image:  docker images | grep simpleresume
#      If missing (from repo root):  docker compose build texlive
#      Or:  docker build -f docker/texlive-full/Dockerfile -t simpleresume-texlive:full .
#   2) Make sure the two lines below are in api/.env, then restart the API.
#   3) curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8000/health | jq .compiler
#      OK if latex_docker_ready == true and latex_docker_image == simpleresume-texlive:full.
#
# Docker Desktop must be running and `docker` must be on PATH.
LATEX_DOCKER_IMAGE=simpleresume-texlive:full
LATEX_DOCKER_NETWORK=none
# Rare: retry with a preamble variant that drops fullpage/glyphtounicode
# LATEX_PORTABLE_PREAMBLE=1

# After /generate: compile PDF and re-prompt if >1 page (needs working Docker compile). 0 = off.
# RESUME_ONE_PAGE_MAX_REVISIONS=3

# Full 1-page density: after PDF is exactly 1 page, rasterize bottom (pdftoppm + Pillow) and
# re-prompt to densify if too much whitespace. 0 = skip. Host needs: brew install poppler (pdftoppm).
# RESUME_DENSITY_EXPAND_MAX=2
# RESUME_UNDERFULL_BOTTOM_FRAC=0.15
# RESUME_UNDERFULL_MEAN_THRESHOLD=233
# RESUME_UNDERFULL_DPI=100
# Overleaf "max full 1 page" baseline (optional): measure your golden PDF:
#   cd api && python scripts/measure_pdf_bottom_mean.py ~/Downloads/your-resume.pdf
# Then paste the printed RESUME_UNDERFULL_GOLDEN_MEAN (when set, absolute threshold is ignored).
# RESUME_UNDERFULL_GOLDEN_MEAN=205.0
# RESUME_UNDERFULL_GOLDEN_MARGIN=12

# ATS: after 1-page PDF OK, pdftotext/pypdf smoke; auto-fix heading/order issues via LLM (0 = off).
# RESUME_ATS_FIX_MAX=2
# Extra LLM pass: diagnostic JSON only (issues), no rewrite. 0/false = off.
# RESUME_QUALITY_CHECKER=false

# LLM returns resume_data JSON only; server builds LaTeX (fewer compile failures). false = legacy latex_document.
# RESUME_STRUCTURED_LATEX=true
# After invalid resume_data, LLM fix_schema retries (0 = fail immediately).
# RESUME_SCHEMA_HEAL_MAX=2

# --- Additive features (default off; see docs/AI_GOVERNANCE.md) ---
# FEATURE_PDF_ANNOTATIONS=false
# FEATURE_ADVANCED_DIAGNOSTICS=false
